422/1908-02-26/ed-1/?fo=json&sp=1", "results": "2 - 2", "to": 2, "total": 8}, "previous_resource": {"label": "Previous Issue", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84020422/1908-02-19/ed-1/?fo=json&sp=1"}, "related_items": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://lccn.loc.gov/2013593082", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2013593082/", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/ff277816-a9a2-5ce3-9a1f-1e53adb03872", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.gmd/g3833k.la000069", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/g3833k.la000069/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["r.p. smith's map manufactory", "skinner, j. l.", "french, j. h. (john homer)", "byles, a. d."], "date": "1859", "dates": ["1859"], "description": ["General-content county map showing hundreds (townships), rural buildings, and householders' names; the town insets show real-property tracts (lots), building coverage, and owners' names. Hand col. to emphasize hundred boundaries/territories and insets. \"Entered according to Act of Congress by J.H. Byles in the year 1859 in the ... Eastern District of Pennsylvania.\" LC copy imperfect: Brittle, shellacked, cracked, darkened, cloth hemmed at outer edges. Includes statistical table, local business directories, and 11 town/village insets (including Dover, Milford, Smyrna, Camden, Frederica). LC Land ownership maps, 69 Available also through the Library of Congress Web site as a raster image. 2 copies"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-04-29T15:39:26.014Z", "group": ["gmd.mar", "catalog-split-01", "catalog", "general-maps", "main-catalog-split-01"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2013593082/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/gmd/gmd383/g3833/g3833k/la000069.gif", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/gmd/gmd383/g3833/g3833k/la000069.gif#h=168&w=150", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:gmd:gmd383:g3833:g3833k:la000069/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=2248&w=2005", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:gmd:gmd383:g3833:g3833k:la000069/full/pct:25/0/default.jpg#h=4496&w=4010"], "index": 2, "language": ["english"], "location": ["milford", "delaware", "dover", "camden", "kent county", "united states", "smyrna", "frederica"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "image/tiff", "image/jpeg", "image/jp2"], "number": ["sheet", "2013-06-01t16:02:58", "2025-06-07t05:29:43.500000", "2013593082"], "online_format": ["image"], "original_format": ["map"], "partof": ["cultural landscapes", "county landownership maps", "catalog", "geography and map division"], "score": 34.64721, "shelf_id": "G3833.K4 1859 .F7 G3833.K4 1859 .F7 Copy 2", "site": ["catalog"], "subject": ["milford", "camden", "milford (del.)", "smyrna", "delaware", "villages", "camden (del.)", "landowners", "kent county", "cities and towns", "real property", "smyrna (del.)", "united states", "frederica", "dover", "frederica (del.)", "cadastral maps", "dover (del.)", "kent county (del.)", "maps"], "timestamp": "2026-04-29T16:08:01.898Z", "title": "Map of Kent County, Delaware : from actual surveys", "type": ["cartographic"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2013593082/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://lccn.loc.gov/2021756482", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2021756482/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/highsm.68261", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/highsm.68261/", "https://www.loc.gov/pictures/item/2021756482/", "http://www.loc.gov/pictures/item/2021756482/", "https://www.loc.gov/pictures/collection/highsm/item/2021756482/", "http://www.loc.gov/pictures/collection/highsm/item/2021756482/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/highsm.68261"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["highsmith, carol m."], "date": "2021-01-01", "dates": ["2021"], "description": ["Title, date, and keywords based on information provided by the photographer. The leather-goods store does not carry boots because, the owner says, every other leather or western store in the county, and especially in nearby Nashville, the center of American country music, ca